1
00:00:00,120 --> 00:00:00,880
Ateş...

2
00:00:00,880 --> 00:00:02,320
Ateş said he loves me.

3
00:00:03,320 --> 00:00:05,320
Oh, Ateş, oh.

4
00:00:06,040 --> 00:00:07,360
What did you say?

5
00:00:08,680 --> 00:00:13,040
What could I say? I made an excuse and ran.

6
00:00:13,760 --> 00:00:15,320
You really did that?

7
00:00:15,920 --> 00:00:18,160
The more she stays silent, the more she’ll remember.

8
00:00:19,320 --> 00:00:20,240
And as she remembers...

9
00:00:20,240 --> 00:00:22,240
you’re being unfair to yourself.

10
00:00:22,240 --> 00:00:26,760
What matters isn’t sweet words.

11
00:00:27,240 --> 00:00:29,880
What matters is standing by them in hard times.

12
00:00:30,200 --> 00:00:31,720
You already did that.

13
00:00:32,280 --> 00:00:34,800
Ateş declared his love in the garden.

14
00:00:35,720 --> 00:00:36,680
It’s over then.

15
00:00:36,920 --> 00:00:38,080
Nothing is over.

16
00:00:38,400 --> 00:00:41,400
I found the necklace you asked about.

17
00:00:41,520 --> 00:00:42,840
At a jeweler friend.

18
00:00:43,000 --> 00:00:44,240
I bought it and sent it.

19
00:00:44,400 --> 00:00:46,080
My friend said that a woman brought it.

20
00:00:46,600 --> 00:00:49,520
Thieving snake, I knew it.

21
00:00:50,320 --> 00:00:51,360
What are you saying?

22
00:00:52,040 --> 00:00:53,280
I didn’t steal anything.

23
00:00:53,400 --> 00:00:54,560
You didn’t, huh?

24
00:00:55,040 --> 00:00:55,840
What’s this then?

25
00:00:56,600 --> 00:00:58,800
I can’t believe you.

26
00:00:59,480 --> 00:01:00,600
Didn’t you think of me?

27
00:01:01,440 --> 00:01:03,000
Is money everything?

28
00:01:03,600 --> 00:01:08,440
is having a family who throws their children into fire.

29
00:01:09,040 --> 00:01:10,360
I opened my heart.

30
00:01:10,600 --> 00:01:13,600
Don’t you see what your silence does to me?

31
00:01:13,880 --> 00:01:15,520
I thought all day.

32
00:01:16,240 --> 00:01:17,240
About how it will be.

33
00:01:17,960 --> 00:01:19,480
You tell me.

34
00:01:20,240 --> 00:01:21,360
Will we forget everything?

35
00:01:21,640 --> 00:01:22,640
There’s no us, Ateş.

36
00:01:29,240 --> 00:01:31,280
Just like we shattered everything else...

37
00:01:32,960 --> 00:01:34,440
...let this break too.

38
00:01:34,680 --> 00:01:36,600
You’ve been getting pretty sharp-tongued lately.

39
00:01:37,560 --> 00:01:39,280
If you’re counting on Ateş, you’re wasting your time.

40
00:01:39,600 --> 00:01:42,480
One day he says he loves you, the next he turns his back.

41
00:01:43,160 --> 00:01:48,560
If we can’t shake Ateş’s trust in Mercan, we’ll shake Mercan’s trust in Ateş.

42
00:01:50,520 --> 00:01:53,360
I’ll show Mercan that Ateş isn’t trustworthy.

43
00:01:54,400 --> 00:01:55,200
Ateş.

44
00:01:56,200 --> 00:01:57,800
Look who I brought.

45
00:02:02,200 --> 00:02:06,400
Still the same successful workaholic Ateş.

46
00:03:25,880 --> 00:03:28,760
Excuse me, sorry to bother you.

47
00:03:32,880 --> 00:03:33,840
You didn’t bother me at all.

48
00:03:48,200 --> 00:03:49,200
Hello.

49
00:04:04,080 --> 00:04:04,520
Hello.

50
00:04:11,600 --> 00:04:14,440
Why did you come? Did you want to say something?

51
00:04:16,520 --> 00:04:18,880
Yes. But I forgot now.

52
00:04:19,680 --> 00:04:21,160
I’ll drop by again when I remember.

53
00:04:25,720 --> 00:04:27,560
We still haven’t been introduced.

54
00:04:37,480 --> 00:04:38,880
I’m Monika.

55
00:04:40,440 --> 00:04:43,160
Monika is Aslı’s friend from the US.

56
00:04:43,880 --> 00:04:47,480
Ateş, shame on you. Am I only Aslı’s friend?

57
00:04:47,640 --> 00:04:49,040
As if you don’t know her.

58
00:04:57,600 --> 00:04:59,040
Let me introduce you. Mercan.

59
00:05:01,720 --> 00:05:02,520
He didn’t say "my wife."

60
00:05:17,200 --> 00:05:22,040
Mercan Karahan. I’m Ateş’s wife. Nice to meet you.

61
00:05:25,280 --> 00:05:25,840
Likewise.

62
00:05:27,840 --> 00:05:31,680
Ateş’s wife? Why did I say it like that just now?

63
00:05:39,520 --> 00:05:43,960
Anyway, I should get going. I have a few things to take care of. Make yourselves comfortable.

64
00:05:55,400 --> 00:05:58,400
What’s going on, Ms. Mercan? Did you need something from Ateş?

65
00:06:05,040 --> 00:06:09,680
He’s a bit busy. I thought I’d work from home.

66
00:06:15,040 --> 00:06:18,760
Tell Mr. Ateş I’ll send it once I finish the revision.

67
00:06:20,240 --> 00:06:22,200
You’ve met Monika, I guess.

68
00:06:25,320 --> 00:06:27,720
Monika’s here? I’ll go say hello.

69
00:06:36,840 --> 00:06:39,880
I don’t know if Ateş told you, but…

70
00:06:39,880 --> 00:06:44,040
When we were in the US, Monika and Ateş were quite close.

71
00:06:45,200 --> 00:06:46,440
Very close.

72
00:06:47,400 --> 00:06:49,400
So close.

73
00:06:51,640 --> 00:06:53,160
May God increase their bond.

74
00:06:54,400 --> 00:06:58,480
Why are you telling me this? What’s it to me?

75
00:07:00,480 --> 00:07:02,720
Of course, what’s it to you?

76
00:07:13,080 --> 00:07:17,800
I missed you so much, Ateş. I almost turned down Aslı’s invitation.

77
00:07:30,400 --> 00:07:32,000
Now I’m glad I came.

78
00:08:03,600 --> 00:08:04,640
You weren’t worth it.

79
00:08:17,560 --> 00:08:21,160
I can’t believe you, brother. And with that girl, of all people.

80
00:08:26,720 --> 00:08:30,360
Make a decision soon. I can’t wait any longer.

81
00:08:31,360 --> 00:08:35,400
One day you’ll slip up and tell your mother everything.

82
00:08:36,240 --> 00:08:38,240
Then God knows what your mother will do to you.

83
00:08:39,800 --> 00:08:41,240
You don’t have much time, keep that in mind.

84
00:08:42,440 --> 00:08:47,600
No way. That girl is a nightmare. She’s taken over our lives.

85
00:09:02,520 --> 00:09:05,880
Come on, come on. Park the car. Park it.

86
00:09:06,520 --> 00:09:07,440
What’s going on, girl?

87
00:09:07,440 --> 00:09:09,440
I was waiting for you too.

88
00:09:09,800 --> 00:09:11,000
What happened? Did something happen to my mom?

89
00:09:11,120 --> 00:09:17,800
No, no, she’s fine. She’s fine, but after what I saw, I’m not fine at all.

90
00:09:19,360 --> 00:09:21,520
Çiçek, what are you talking about? Don’t beat around the bush, say it straight.

91
00:09:21,520 --> 00:09:23,600
What’s going on between you and Zehra?

92
00:09:25,320 --> 00:09:27,960
You froze. Was that too blunt?

93
00:09:29,040 --> 00:09:32,600
What are you saying, Çiçek? You made a fool of me here.

94
00:09:33,600 --> 00:09:36,760
I asked you a question, brother, and I’m waiting for an answer.

95
00:09:37,560 --> 00:09:39,280
What kind of answer do you expect?

96
00:09:39,840 --> 00:09:43,440
You could say there is something between me and Zehra, or there isn’t.

97
00:09:45,480 --> 00:09:46,800
I plead the right to remain silent.

98
00:09:47,920 --> 00:09:51,080
Brother, is there something or not?

99
00:09:51,960 --> 00:09:55,200
There might be, or there might not be.

100
00:09:55,840 --> 00:09:57,200
Will you be honest, please?

101
00:09:58,200 --> 00:10:02,080
What’s going on, Çiçek? Are we in court? You’re interrogating me.

102
00:10:02,320 --> 00:10:03,800
And what’s it to you anyway?

103
00:10:04,640 --> 00:10:07,280
Well well, what’s happening? Looks like the lines got crossed in the Black Sea.

104
00:10:07,400 --> 00:10:08,240
Pull yourself together.

105
00:10:09,520 --> 00:10:10,440
I’m your brother.

106
00:10:13,520 --> 00:10:15,040
I got you. I understand.

107
00:10:16,800 --> 00:10:20,840
The only thing I don’t get is how you believe Zehra.

108
00:10:21,240 --> 00:10:22,760
We’re talking about Zehra, brother.

109
00:10:23,360 --> 00:10:27,440
Çiçek, someone might hear, keep your voice down.

110
00:10:28,040 --> 00:10:29,800
We just sat and had tea, that’s all.

111
00:10:30,480 --> 00:10:33,720
Hasn’t this girl put us through hell since she came to the mansion?

112
00:10:34,400 --> 00:10:36,160
There’s nothing she hasn’t said or done.

113
00:10:37,320 --> 00:10:40,560
And now you go and see her. Does that make sense?

114
00:10:41,760 --> 00:10:44,080
Zehra has changed a lot. She’s not like before.

115
00:10:44,080 --> 00:10:48,120
Her heart turned soft, like cotton.

116
00:10:49,240 --> 00:10:49,800
Cotton?

117
00:10:50,320 --> 00:10:50,840
Cotton.

118
00:10:51,040 --> 00:10:53,240
Zehra… soft like cotton, huh?

119
00:10:53,320 --> 00:10:53,600
Yes.

120
00:10:54,120 --> 00:10:55,640
Not thorny, like a thorn.

121
00:10:56,960 --> 00:10:58,640
You’re completely smitten.

122
00:10:58,720 --> 00:11:01,960
Watch your mouth. You’re talking behind her back, taking on her sin.

123
00:11:02,680 --> 00:11:05,760
The girl turned sweet and gentle.

124
00:11:06,320 --> 00:11:09,840
If you saw her, honey dripping from her mouth.

125
00:11:11,800 --> 00:11:15,440
Brother, turn back from this mistake while you still can.

126
00:11:16,240 --> 00:11:19,520
Çiçek, there’s no mistake here.

127
00:11:19,880 --> 00:11:22,360
No mistake, and no turning back.

128
00:11:22,520 --> 00:11:24,400
We’re on a path now.

129
00:11:25,120 --> 00:11:27,000
So whatever I say is pointless, right?

130
00:11:28,760 --> 00:11:30,440
It’s hard to believe, of course.

131
00:11:30,720 --> 00:11:32,920
But what can you do, the heart doesn’t listen to reason.

132
00:11:34,000 --> 00:11:35,520
We love each other.

133
00:11:36,680 --> 00:11:37,280
Oh no.

134
00:11:37,280 --> 00:11:40,280
Oh no, and now he says we’re in love.

135
00:11:41,480 --> 00:11:43,040
What, shouldn’t I have said it?

136
00:11:44,080 --> 00:11:44,680
Brother.

137
00:11:45,480 --> 00:11:49,000
What do you mean brother? When you love someone it’s fine, but when we do it’s a problem?

138
00:11:49,560 --> 00:11:51,360
That girl really scrambled your head.

139
00:11:52,840 --> 00:11:53,920
This won’t work.

140
00:11:54,480 --> 00:11:55,400
Listen to me.

141
00:11:56,600 --> 00:11:58,520
Çiçek, look at me.

142
00:11:58,800 --> 00:12:00,160
I’m leaving now.

143
00:12:00,520 --> 00:12:03,120
But I’ll be back. We’ll talk about this, don’t think it’s over.

144
00:12:03,680 --> 00:12:05,680
Fine, we’ll talk. Put the kettle on.

145
00:12:08,280 --> 00:12:10,440
Look at those moves.

146
00:12:11,840 --> 00:12:13,840
She drove me crazy for no reason.

147
00:12:16,840 --> 00:12:18,760
Patience, God give me patience.

148
00:12:21,040 --> 00:12:24,040
You dyed your hair red back then.

149
00:12:24,320 --> 00:12:25,560
Do you remember that day?

150
00:12:26,440 --> 00:12:27,320
I don’t remember.

151
00:12:28,560 --> 00:12:29,880
Let’s give credit where it’s due.

152
00:12:30,160 --> 00:12:32,360
You were the most sensible one among us.

153
00:12:45,040 --> 00:12:47,760
Look at him, charisma from head to toe.

154
00:12:53,240 --> 00:12:56,240
Aslı, why don’t you take her downstairs to the cafeteria?

155
00:12:56,360 --> 00:12:58,960
They make decent lattes and stuff. Show her around.

156
00:12:59,280 --> 00:13:00,800
She might be curious.

157
00:13:00,800 --> 00:13:03,720
Yeah, that’d be good. Flying really affects me.

158
00:13:06,120 --> 00:13:06,760
Sure.

159
00:13:07,360 --> 00:13:08,360
Come on, let’s wake you up.

160
00:13:10,640 --> 00:13:12,120
You’ve flown enough already.

161
00:13:29,120 --> 00:13:29,560
Finally.

162
00:13:30,560 --> 00:13:31,800
I thought they’d never leave.

163
00:13:32,880 --> 00:13:33,480
What do you mean, brother?

164
00:13:34,160 --> 00:13:35,200
Honestly, I was fed up too.

165
00:13:43,480 --> 00:13:45,720
Your purpose here is clear.

166
00:13:46,360 --> 00:13:48,320
You’re here to drive a wedge between Ateş and Mercan.

167
00:13:48,840 --> 00:13:49,960
To split them up.

168
00:13:51,320 --> 00:13:53,680
Just don’t get carried away with the role.

169
00:13:54,640 --> 00:13:55,520
Let’s not fall out.

170
00:13:59,520 --> 00:14:00,880
Hopefully this visit won’t last long, Insallah.

171
00:14:01,760 --> 00:14:04,240
I never liked this girl anyway.

172
00:14:07,680 --> 00:14:09,240
But she’s Aslı’s guest.

173
00:14:09,880 --> 00:14:10,880
We’ll have to put up with it.

174
00:14:12,320 --> 00:14:15,920
She’s a bit clingy, but we’ll manage for a few days.

175
00:14:21,640 --> 00:14:22,720
Why are you in a bad mood?

176
00:14:23,600 --> 00:14:24,560
Maybe you should talk to Mercan again.

177
00:14:26,960 --> 00:14:28,560
There’s nothing to talk about, Cemal.

178
00:14:29,560 --> 00:14:30,640
I said what I had to say.

179
00:14:32,520 --> 00:14:34,480
Mercan made her stance clear too.

180
00:14:35,160 --> 00:14:36,240
You can’t force feelings.

181
00:14:38,720 --> 00:14:40,360
I just can’t wrap my head around this.

182
00:14:41,480 --> 00:14:43,560
I’m sure Mercan loves you.

183
00:14:47,320 --> 00:14:48,800
Maybe you misunderstood what she said.

184
00:14:49,880 --> 00:14:51,240
Don’t wind me up, Cemal.

185
00:14:51,560 --> 00:14:52,200
I’m done.

186
00:14:53,440 --> 00:14:55,400
If she wanted to say how she felt, she would have.

187
00:15:00,200 --> 00:15:01,800
She was uncomfortable that day, it showed.

188
00:15:06,160 --> 00:15:09,800
Just now she was acting strange too.

189
00:15:09,960 --> 00:15:10,960
I can’t say my mind is at ease.

190
00:15:17,480 --> 00:15:19,080
I’ll go check on her.

191
00:15:20,240 --> 00:15:23,240
Don’t bother. Mercan isn’t here, she left.

192
00:15:23,720 --> 00:15:25,200
She said she’d work from home.

193
00:15:29,280 --> 00:15:31,040
She left without waiting for me?

194
00:15:36,680 --> 00:15:37,600
She could’ve at least told me.

195
00:15:59,680 --> 00:16:01,840
Any news about Ateş’s sibling?

196
00:16:02,640 --> 00:16:04,240
I couldn’t find anything, Haydar.

197
00:16:04,520 --> 00:16:05,400
The man’s like a ghost.

198
00:16:06,560 --> 00:16:07,800
You didn’t dig deep enough.

199
00:16:10,400 --> 00:16:12,200
I know my job, Haydar.

200
00:16:12,320 --> 00:16:13,080
You know that.

201
00:16:13,280 --> 00:16:14,480
No one knows anything.

202
00:16:16,240 --> 00:16:17,280
What does that mean?

203
00:16:18,800 --> 00:16:19,920
I’m being clear.

204
00:16:20,440 --> 00:16:22,440
Ateş has no sibling.

205
00:16:23,240 --> 00:16:25,240
Your source might be lying.

206
00:16:25,240 --> 00:16:28,880
Or there’s something else going on.

207
00:16:29,480 --> 00:16:31,560
Stop circling it and say it straight.

208
00:16:33,520 --> 00:16:39,200
Either your information is wrong, or Ateş isn’t Ateş.

209
00:16:40,040 --> 00:16:41,560
What do you mean Ateş isn’t Ateş?

210
00:16:42,680 --> 00:16:45,120
It means such a person doesn’t exist.

211
00:16:46,040 --> 00:16:47,280
As if he never lived.

212
00:16:51,640 --> 00:16:53,000
What is this man up to?

213
00:16:54,440 --> 00:16:56,640
What kind of schemes are spinning around me?

214
00:16:59,160 --> 00:17:00,800
We need to move fast, Ziya.

215
00:17:02,080 --> 00:17:03,880
We need results, and soon.

216
00:17:04,560 --> 00:17:07,600
I told you, this is life or death for me.

217
00:17:09,160 --> 00:17:11,640
We’ll find it, but Haydar…

218
00:17:12,800 --> 00:17:16,320
This kind of work doesn’t come cheap.

219
00:17:17,000 --> 00:17:18,920
You’ll have to open your wallet.

220
00:17:20,040 --> 00:17:21,160
What are you saying, Ziya?

221
00:17:22,800 --> 00:17:24,440
I just handed over a wad of cash.

222
00:17:24,600 --> 00:17:26,040
I’ve got nothing left.

223
00:17:27,040 --> 00:17:29,360
No money, no job.

224
00:17:30,600 --> 00:17:32,080
We don’t run on water.

225
00:17:34,360 --> 00:17:37,920
I’ve got men working the streets for me, all waiting on me.

226
00:17:39,800 --> 00:17:43,760
Fine. I’ll handle it. Just find something.

227
00:17:56,520 --> 00:18:00,680
Come here, Leyla. Where have you been, girl?

228
00:18:02,000 --> 00:18:04,040
Out and about, my dear?

229
00:18:04,040 --> 00:18:07,280
Oh my precious. What did you do?

230
00:18:07,960 --> 00:18:09,200
Is your food and water there?

231
00:18:10,200 --> 00:18:11,160
Come here.

232
00:18:12,040 --> 00:18:14,720
See? They didn’t put out your water.

233
00:18:16,160 --> 00:18:19,000
They don’t know these things. Come here.

234
00:18:19,280 --> 00:18:20,240
Let’s freshen it up.

235
00:18:21,200 --> 00:18:21,800
Hold on.

236
00:18:24,120 --> 00:18:25,320
Come here.

237
00:18:25,960 --> 00:18:28,920
Did they give you food and water while I was gone?

238
00:18:29,800 --> 00:18:31,680
Or did you go rummaging through trash?

239
00:18:32,640 --> 00:18:35,720
Look, no water. Come on, let’s fix it.

240
00:18:37,160 --> 00:18:37,600
There.

241
00:18:38,280 --> 00:18:39,640
Drink up, nice and clean.

242
00:18:40,120 --> 00:18:41,680
Drink, my Leyla.

243
00:18:42,800 --> 00:18:45,160
Easy now, don’t fuss.

244
00:18:45,680 --> 00:18:46,400
Come on.

245
00:18:46,920 --> 00:18:47,560
Come here.

246
00:18:48,320 --> 00:18:51,000
I got the one you like, salmon flavor.

247
00:18:51,520 --> 00:18:53,480
You like fish, just like me, don’t you?

248
00:18:54,240 --> 00:18:55,360
Good girl.

249
00:18:56,840 --> 00:18:57,640
Enjoy.

250
00:18:57,880 --> 00:19:00,080
Oh my beautiful girl.

251
00:19:00,080 --> 00:19:01,800
What a creation.

252
00:19:02,760 --> 00:19:03,920
Well done.

253
00:19:06,120 --> 00:19:07,520
Eat your fill.

254
00:19:07,880 --> 00:19:09,400
Don’t go digging in trash, my dear.

255
00:19:11,320 --> 00:19:12,840
Eat a bit more.

256
00:19:13,800 --> 00:19:15,600
Why are you staring at me like that?

257
00:19:15,760 --> 00:19:17,000
I got sick, what can I do?

258
00:19:19,880 --> 00:19:21,120
Enjoy your meal, my darling.

259
00:19:22,160 --> 00:19:23,080
Come on.

260
00:19:24,000 --> 00:19:25,880
Come back again, I’ll put out your water.

261
00:19:27,160 --> 00:19:28,640
Oh my precious.

262
00:19:39,560 --> 00:19:40,480
Stop.

263
00:19:40,920 --> 00:19:41,560
Stop like that.

264
00:19:42,760 --> 00:19:44,280
Go on now.

265
00:19:53,960 --> 00:19:55,080
Oh Çiçek, oh.

266
00:20:03,800 --> 00:20:04,600
You’ve grown up.

267
00:20:07,040 --> 00:20:08,320
Oh my.

268
00:20:10,160 --> 00:20:14,880
Did I make the right decision, or will their separation cause harm?

269
00:20:16,360 --> 00:20:18,200
Being a mother is so hard.

270
00:20:18,200 --> 00:20:21,440
Would anyone ever want their child to be hurt?

271
00:20:27,720 --> 00:20:29,480
Oh my Lord, you are great.

272
00:20:30,440 --> 00:20:33,600
You know what’s best, what’s most righteous.

273
00:20:34,240 --> 00:20:36,760
Grant that for my children.

274
00:20:42,040 --> 00:20:43,760
Oh my daughter.

275
00:20:51,360 --> 00:20:55,200
My dear mother, you’re a true Black Sea woman.

276
00:20:57,320 --> 00:20:58,920
A real Black Sea mother.

277
00:21:00,360 --> 00:21:03,000
Come, my son, welcome. My brave boy.

278
00:21:03,800 --> 00:21:07,200
Mom, didn’t you get up early?

279
00:21:08,080 --> 00:21:10,840
Enough already, sleeping and sleeping. How long?

280
00:21:10,920 --> 00:21:13,800
Lying in bed makes me sicker.

281
00:21:14,360 --> 00:21:16,800
All right, mom, if you say so.

282
00:21:17,320 --> 00:21:19,640
How are you? Are you hungry?

283
00:21:19,960 --> 00:21:22,920
I’m hungry, mom. That’s why I came.

284
00:21:23,560 --> 00:21:25,840
Let’s eat something together.

285
00:21:26,320 --> 00:21:28,520
Let’s eat well, my son. I’ll heat some food.

286
00:21:28,760 --> 00:21:30,920
No, no. You won’t do anything.

287
00:21:30,920 --> 00:21:33,120
You sit, I’ll prepare it.

288
00:21:33,760 --> 00:21:37,480
It’s not that hard, I’m not throwing stones.

289
00:21:37,680 --> 00:21:38,680
I’ll just heat two dishes.

290
00:21:38,880 --> 00:21:43,240
No, mom. You'll be off duty for a while.

291
00:21:43,560 --> 00:21:46,200
Berat Güneş signed off on it. That’s how it is now.

292
00:21:46,720 --> 00:21:47,640
Come on.

293
00:21:47,640 --> 00:21:48,800
My good son.

294
00:21:49,000 --> 00:21:49,880
Come, my dear.

295
00:21:51,320 --> 00:21:51,920
You’re okay, right?

296
00:21:52,240 --> 00:21:54,640
I’m fine, my lion. Come in.

297
00:23:08,520 --> 00:23:10,280
It’s my fault.

298
00:23:10,920 --> 00:23:13,040
I was even going to apologize to the gentleman.

299
00:23:14,440 --> 00:23:15,600
What do you expect from a fickle heart?

300
00:23:16,880 --> 00:23:20,160
If you’ve got eyes for other women, why say you love me?

301
00:23:34,400 --> 00:23:35,920
Why didn’t you wait for me?

302
00:23:37,040 --> 00:23:38,200
Was I supposed to?

303
00:23:38,600 --> 00:23:40,800
Of course. Why go alone?

304
00:23:41,440 --> 00:23:42,400
What kind of question is that?

305
00:23:43,040 --> 00:23:43,960
I’m not a child.

306
00:23:44,760 --> 00:23:46,600
I don’t need anyone to hold my hand.

307
00:23:48,360 --> 00:23:49,800
You know that’s not what I meant.

308
00:23:50,640 --> 00:23:53,400
When will you learn you can’t just do whatever you want?

309
00:23:55,480 --> 00:23:57,720
You know I don’t like this.

310
00:23:59,560 --> 00:24:01,480
Fine. Next time I’ll let you know, Mr. Ateş.

311
00:24:03,120 --> 00:24:04,320
I’m serious.

312
00:24:05,760 --> 00:24:06,800
We had work to do.

313
00:24:09,360 --> 00:24:11,600
And why did you go alone, without security?

314
00:24:12,200 --> 00:24:13,440
After everything that happened to you.

315
00:24:17,520 --> 00:24:18,920
Nothing will happen to me, don’t worry.

316
00:24:20,040 --> 00:24:21,680
And if it does, you’ll be rid of me anyway.

317
00:24:21,680 --> 00:24:23,680
God forbid. What kind of talk is that?

318
00:24:26,560 --> 00:24:28,080
Don’t act without telling me again.

319
00:24:30,280 --> 00:24:31,960
I didn’t want to bother you.

320
00:24:33,240 --> 00:24:36,560
There wasn’t much left, I thought I’d finish at home.

321
00:24:37,520 --> 00:24:39,320
At least you could have said something before leaving.

322
00:24:40,560 --> 00:24:43,880
I was going to, but you were busy with your guest.

323
00:24:44,520 --> 00:24:46,000
I didn’t want to interrupt.

324
00:24:46,800 --> 00:24:47,640
What guest?

325
00:24:50,480 --> 00:24:53,040
The American one.

326
00:24:54,240 --> 00:24:56,320
The one you sat at the table.

327
00:24:57,920 --> 00:25:00,840
Monika isn’t my guest, she’s Aslı’s.

328
00:25:01,800 --> 00:25:03,440
I don’t care who she is.

329
00:25:04,640 --> 00:25:06,480
It didn’t look like that to me.

330
00:25:08,040 --> 00:25:08,800
How so?

331
00:25:11,520 --> 00:25:13,760
I’m not going to discuss this now.

332
00:25:14,240 --> 00:25:15,640
It’s not even worth discussing.

333
00:25:16,440 --> 00:25:19,200
I’ve got a lot on my plate.

334
00:25:19,840 --> 00:25:21,600
I want to get this done as soon as possible.

335
00:25:23,640 --> 00:25:25,760
We were supposed to work together, you just left.

336
00:25:27,040 --> 00:25:28,360
I already told you why.

337
00:25:28,960 --> 00:25:30,520
No need to repeat it.

338
00:25:34,960 --> 00:25:37,000
Anyway, I can’t deal with this now.

339
00:25:37,400 --> 00:25:39,000
I’ll focus on my work. You should too.

340
00:25:41,600 --> 00:25:41,960
Fine.

341
00:25:43,560 --> 00:25:44,760
I will, but…

342
00:25:49,240 --> 00:25:50,680
Your place is by my side.

343
00:25:52,160 --> 00:25:54,720
You’re my employee.

344
00:25:55,680 --> 00:25:57,080
That’s what work ethics require, right?

345
00:25:58,560 --> 00:25:59,520
Work ethics?

346
00:26:00,320 --> 00:26:02,280
Maybe you should question yourself first.

347
00:26:03,160 --> 00:26:07,080
I walked into your office to work and saw something else entirely.

348
00:26:07,800 --> 00:26:08,920
What kind of work ethic is that?

349
00:26:10,760 --> 00:26:13,040
You thought for me and reached a conclusion?

350
00:26:14,520 --> 00:26:17,480
What I saw was clear enough.

351
00:26:17,600 --> 00:26:19,080
You’re wrong.

352
00:26:20,120 --> 00:26:21,400
If I am, I am.

353
00:26:21,800 --> 00:26:23,080
My mistake, my truth.

354
00:26:24,640 --> 00:26:26,640
I run this company, okay?

355
00:26:27,400 --> 00:26:29,320
I make the final calls.

356
00:26:30,360 --> 00:26:31,720
On mistakes and on what’s right.

357
00:26:32,760 --> 00:26:33,920
All right, Mr. Ateş.

358
00:26:35,000 --> 00:26:39,280
But instead of questioning me, maybe review your own decisions.

359
00:26:40,080 --> 00:26:44,160
While we have an urgent presentation to revise, you’re hosting guests from America.

360
00:26:45,480 --> 00:26:49,440
Monika isn’t my guest, she’s Aslı’s.

361
00:26:54,120 --> 00:26:54,960
And…

362
00:26:54,960 --> 00:26:57,160
Are you jealous of Monika?

363
00:26:58,720 --> 00:27:01,600
Jealous? Where did that come from?

364
00:27:02,560 --> 00:27:05,200
What are you, the most handsome man alive? Why would I be jealous?

365
00:27:06,680 --> 00:27:07,240
I don’t know.

366
00:27:10,480 --> 00:27:11,200
You tell me.

367
00:27:13,280 --> 00:27:16,920
Don’t ask. Don’t ask me things like that.

368
00:27:21,520 --> 00:27:23,720
I just meant…

369
00:27:25,080 --> 00:27:31,480
Since you hosted her in your office, it looked like you enjoyed it.

370
00:27:36,320 --> 00:27:38,800
You could’ve politely sent her away, saying it’s work hours.

371
00:27:39,360 --> 00:27:41,200
Or whatever, it’s none of my business.

372
00:27:41,800 --> 00:27:42,560
That’s all.

373
00:27:46,720 --> 00:27:52,400
I can host you in my office too. Maybe I already sent her away. How would you know?

374
00:27:54,920 --> 00:28:00,640
I don’t know. But you were deep in conversation. I doubt it.

375
00:28:07,080 --> 00:28:08,480
Is it really about work?

376
00:28:10,440 --> 00:28:12,320
Or is there something else behind this anger?

377
00:28:13,360 --> 00:28:19,800
What could it be? My mind is on work, nothing else.

378
00:28:36,440 --> 00:28:37,760
I think you’re jealous.

379
00:28:40,520 --> 00:28:41,920
I told you I have work.

380
00:28:46,840 --> 00:28:55,120
Fine. Good luck with it then. Jealous.

381
00:28:55,120 --> 00:28:57,120
(U) Thanks.

382
00:29:09,920 --> 00:29:16,600
Why would I be jealous of you? Am I jealous?

383
00:29:18,640 --> 00:29:20,640
No. No.

384
00:29:49,440 --> 00:29:52,240
Haydar, I dropped everything and came.

385
00:29:52,560 --> 00:29:54,440
I hope it’s as important as you said.

386
00:29:54,800 --> 00:29:57,400
It is. I need cash urgently.

387
00:29:58,720 --> 00:30:03,480
You called me for this? Take a look, does it say charity?

388
00:30:05,480 --> 00:30:07,000
You already get your share from the company.

389
00:30:07,560 --> 00:30:09,000
I need more.

390
00:30:10,080 --> 00:30:14,840
You should’ve thought of that before losing your assets.

391
00:30:14,880 --> 00:30:17,080
That’s why I want to get rid of him.

392
00:30:17,720 --> 00:30:21,640
I’m having Ateş investigated. Soon the truth will come out.

393
00:30:22,720 --> 00:30:24,160
We’ll see what his game is.

394
00:30:26,080 --> 00:30:26,840
Who’s investigating?

395
00:30:28,320 --> 00:30:33,400
An old pro. He says Ateş might not even exist.

396
00:30:34,600 --> 00:30:35,280
What do you mean?

397
00:30:36,160 --> 00:30:38,280
Like getting a new identity.

398
00:30:39,040 --> 00:30:42,080
I learned Ateş had a brother who died. Firsthand.

399
00:30:42,080 --> 00:30:45,000
But Ziya says Ateş never had a brother.

400
00:30:46,440 --> 00:30:48,440
Why would someone hide himself?

401
00:30:48,760 --> 00:30:50,600
We’ll see when we find out who he is.

402
00:30:54,720 --> 00:30:57,720
Can Ziya find it?

403
00:30:58,720 --> 00:31:01,360
He will. He’s confident.

404
00:31:04,400 --> 00:31:05,480
I knew it.

405
00:31:06,000 --> 00:31:08,640
From the start, I knew Ateş was shady.

406
00:31:10,240 --> 00:31:14,280
Good. Since you’re this close.

407
00:31:15,160 --> 00:31:15,400
Fine.

408
00:31:17,480 --> 00:31:19,480
Let’s see who Ateş Karahan really is.

409
00:31:43,720 --> 00:31:45,360
O Lord of mankind.

410
00:31:47,360 --> 00:31:51,320
O God who removes all troubles.

411
00:31:52,040 --> 00:31:53,760
Do not lead me astray.

412
00:31:55,840 --> 00:31:59,200
Grant goodness, beauty, and health.

413
00:32:00,600 --> 00:32:03,200
Heal aunt Binnaz, my Lord.

414
00:32:04,520 --> 00:32:08,000
You are the healer, none but You can heal.

415
00:32:09,360 --> 00:32:13,560
Grant her such healing that no trace of illness remains.

416
00:32:15,120 --> 00:32:16,640
I seek refuge in You.

417
00:32:17,640 --> 00:32:20,040
You give both illness and cure.

418
00:32:21,120 --> 00:32:25,160
Show a miracle so Çiçek and I may reunite.

419
00:32:27,600 --> 00:32:28,360
Amen.

420
00:32:34,880 --> 00:32:38,720
O God, help us. I ruined everything.

421
00:32:40,360 --> 00:32:42,480
Grant me the chance to fix it.

422
00:32:43,720 --> 00:32:45,960
I wish I had told everything from the start.

423
00:32:46,520 --> 00:32:48,400
Maybe we wouldn’t have separated.

424
00:32:50,520 --> 00:32:51,840
I made a mistake.

425
00:32:52,960 --> 00:32:53,760
We’re only human.

426
00:32:56,400 --> 00:32:58,120
Forgive me, my Lord.

427
00:32:59,960 --> 00:33:01,280
I can’t upset aunt Binnaz anymore.

428
00:33:02,160 --> 00:33:05,400
She’s a mother. I must support her.

429
00:33:06,720 --> 00:33:08,240
And I must do it for Çiçek too.

430
00:33:11,280 --> 00:33:13,160
Show me a way, my Lord.

431
00:33:14,120 --> 00:33:15,600
Time heals all wounds.

432
00:33:15,600 --> 00:33:18,760
With God’s help, these days will pass too, Insallah.

433
00:33:21,520 --> 00:33:22,920
My Lord.

434
00:33:23,840 --> 00:33:25,520
Accept my prayers.

435
00:33:52,520 --> 00:33:55,640
I had hazelnut lahmacun made, since you like it.

436
00:33:56,840 --> 00:33:59,320
Eat it hot, it’s no good cold.

437
00:33:59,720 --> 00:34:02,760
Thank you, Mommy Müzeyyen. You remembered.

438
00:34:03,080 --> 00:34:04,440
I had künefe made too.

439
00:34:04,800 --> 00:34:05,680
Thank you.

440
00:34:06,000 --> 00:34:08,920
How could I forget? Ateş always talked about it.

441
00:34:14,840 --> 00:34:20,800
Especially how Monika loves Turkish desserts, especially künefe.

442
00:34:32,440 --> 00:34:34,640
She still doesn’t know what I like.

443
00:34:35,000 --> 00:34:35,520
Look at that.

444
00:34:37,160 --> 00:34:39,200
Though she guessed baked rice pudding.

445
00:34:40,040 --> 00:34:41,520
She must have guessed.

446
00:34:42,280 --> 00:34:44,600
You’re mixing it up, Müzeyyen. That was Aslı.

447
00:34:46,120 --> 00:34:48,960
Turn it around. Now you say that, but…

448
00:34:48,960 --> 00:34:51,400
Back in college, everyone admired you.

449
00:34:51,720 --> 00:34:52,920
They called you couple of the year.

450
00:34:56,840 --> 00:34:58,000
Couple of the year, huh.

451
00:35:11,400 --> 00:35:13,160
Honey, can you pass the salt?

452
00:35:16,920 --> 00:35:18,720
The food is quite oily.

453
00:35:19,880 --> 00:35:21,960
Is it? Then don’t eat it.

454
00:35:26,160 --> 00:35:27,400
You were so cool.

455
00:35:28,480 --> 00:35:31,520
We were. Girls hated me.

456
00:35:32,520 --> 00:35:35,920
You should’ve seen the looks when I walked with Ateş.

457
00:35:38,120 --> 00:35:40,280
I know. They asked me too.

458
00:35:44,080 --> 00:35:45,560
That’s all in the past, right?

459
00:35:46,560 --> 00:35:49,040
Baby, come on. We looked great.

460
00:36:02,920 --> 00:36:06,080
Anyway. Everyone learned there was nothing between us.

461
00:36:07,040 --> 00:36:09,160
Gather it up. A bit more to the right.

462
00:36:15,560 --> 00:36:18,480
But they kept thinking we were a couple.

463
00:36:18,480 --> 00:36:23,200
We were always together. Alone.

464
00:36:27,880 --> 00:36:30,360
I approved and sent you the revision.

465
00:36:34,080 --> 00:36:34,880
I’ll look later.

466
00:36:37,680 --> 00:36:38,480
I won’t add anything.

467
00:36:38,600 --> 00:36:41,560
We have guests. Maybe not talk work.

468
00:36:46,720 --> 00:36:50,120
I wish we’d known about the guest.

469
00:36:52,200 --> 00:36:57,640
We didn’t need permission to invite guests to our home.

470
00:36:59,080 --> 00:37:01,760
We felt like it and invited her.

471
00:37:14,320 --> 00:37:17,560
Thank you so much. You were always like this.

472
00:37:17,920 --> 00:37:21,120
I’ve never seen anyone as thoughtful as you.

473
00:37:23,600 --> 00:37:26,600
I’ve never seen anyone as thoughtful as you.

474
00:37:32,600 --> 00:37:36,360
Since you’re here, how about a movie night, the four of us?

475
00:37:37,680 --> 00:37:39,320
We never managed before.

476
00:37:43,800 --> 00:37:46,400
I’ll say it upfront, Aslı. No action, I’m not coming.

477
00:37:46,440 --> 00:37:47,720
I can’t stand action movies.

478
00:37:48,520 --> 00:37:49,600
Right, Ateş? What do you say?

479
00:37:54,160 --> 00:37:54,520
We’ll see.

480
00:37:56,920 --> 00:38:02,200
Remember, Ateş, when I visited you in the US?

481
00:38:05,320 --> 00:38:10,440
Aslı wasn’t home. She was staying with a friend.

482
00:38:11,520 --> 00:38:16,440
We watched movies together all night.

483
00:38:16,880 --> 00:38:18,320
It was very romantic.

484
00:38:18,480 --> 00:38:19,840
What was the movie called?

485
00:38:24,080 --> 00:38:25,360
I don’t remember.

486
00:38:29,720 --> 00:38:34,920
Shame on you. You liked it too.

487
00:38:38,160 --> 00:38:40,880
It was a wonderful night.

488
00:38:51,240 --> 00:38:54,960
So that’s your tactic. Movie night.

489
00:39:14,120 --> 00:39:15,120
Enjoy your meal.

490
00:39:20,480 --> 00:39:25,080
I’ll get going too. Enjoy.

491
00:39:39,840 --> 00:39:40,960
Careful, dear.

492
00:39:41,080 --> 00:39:41,840
Sorry, mom.

493
00:39:47,440 --> 00:39:51,720
Thanks, smells great.

494
00:39:59,000 --> 00:40:17,880
Thanks. Çiçek, pass the salt.

495
00:40:23,160 --> 00:40:25,040
Hey, salt. Pass it.

496
00:40:40,840 --> 00:40:42,240
What’s wrong with you two?

497
00:40:44,640 --> 00:40:45,120
With us?

498
00:40:48,040 --> 00:40:49,200
Nothing.

499
00:40:52,400 --> 00:40:55,600
You both look sour. Did you fight?

500
00:40:56,360 --> 00:40:57,000
No.

501
00:40:59,320 --> 00:41:04,240
My brother didn’t do anything bad, right?

502
00:41:04,480 --> 00:41:06,480
Right. If I had, we would have fought.

503
00:41:08,560 --> 00:41:11,360
Of course we would, but you wouldn’t, right?

504
00:41:11,560 --> 00:41:12,320
Would I ever?

505
00:41:12,520 --> 00:41:13,520
I don’t know, would you?

506
00:41:14,640 --> 00:41:15,680
What fault did you see in me?

507
00:41:19,560 --> 00:41:23,280
My reputation’s ruined. Once it’s nine, it never drops to eight.

508
00:41:24,280 --> 00:41:26,760
Maybe you earned that reputation yourself.

509
00:41:28,640 --> 00:41:30,880
You always blamed me, didn’t you?

510
00:41:32,360 --> 00:41:35,040
No, brother. Would I ever blame you?

511
00:41:35,040 --> 00:41:38,520
Let’s eat our soup before it gets cold.

512
00:41:38,800 --> 00:41:42,280
Don’t let it cool, or the mood will sour.

513
00:41:43,480 --> 00:41:45,760
It won’t. If it does, I’ll catch it.

514
00:41:47,080 --> 00:41:49,120
Insallah. May God not let it slip.

515
00:41:50,560 --> 00:41:53,520
If it slips, it’s mine. If it doesn’t, it’s mine.

516
00:41:53,800 --> 00:41:55,480
You never know.

517
00:41:56,560 --> 00:41:57,760
You do know.

518
00:41:58,400 --> 00:42:00,160
Enjoy your meal. Eat.

519
00:42:01,320 --> 00:42:04,880
I’ll eat or not, mind your business, Çiçek.

520
00:42:09,800 --> 00:42:10,840
Enough.

521
00:42:15,000 --> 00:42:18,200
What is this, Karagöz and Hacivat? You didn’t let anyone eat.

522
00:42:27,160 --> 00:42:28,520
Hello, Remziye.

523
00:42:30,840 --> 00:42:31,800
How are you, sister?

524
00:42:34,120 --> 00:42:37,400
I’m fine. I will be fine, Insallah.

525
00:42:38,520 --> 00:42:40,120
What do you think you’re doing?

526
00:42:41,240 --> 00:42:44,480
What am I doing? I’m trying to protect you.

527
00:42:46,240 --> 00:42:48,480
I don’t need protection. Don’t drive me crazy.

528
00:42:49,160 --> 00:42:52,320
She’ll hurt you, and I don’t want that.

529
00:42:52,680 --> 00:42:53,320
You’re wrong.

530
00:42:53,560 --> 00:42:54,920
I’m not. I know.

531
00:42:55,320 --> 00:42:57,040
Zehra loves me.

532
00:42:58,800 --> 00:43:00,800
Zehra loves no one but herself.

533
00:43:01,600 --> 00:43:04,440
Çiçek, I’m older. I’m your brother.

534
00:43:04,560 --> 00:43:06,320
Don’t treat me like a child.

535
00:43:07,000 --> 00:43:07,760
Eat your food.

536
00:43:08,040 --> 00:43:08,680
You eat.

537
00:43:10,440 --> 00:43:11,520
We’re thinking of your good.

538
00:43:12,200 --> 00:43:12,800
She’s here, hush.

539
00:43:13,920 --> 00:43:16,400
The food turned out great, right?

540
00:43:16,480 --> 00:43:20,200
Yes, very good. Well done.

541
00:43:22,480 --> 00:43:23,320
It’s bland.

542
00:43:29,040 --> 00:43:32,680
I’m exhausted. I’m fed up with this.

543
00:43:33,040 --> 00:43:35,920
Enough bickering. I’ll go back to the kitchen tomorrow.

544
00:43:36,400 --> 00:43:37,280
No way.

545
00:43:38,400 --> 00:43:39,720
Well well.

546
00:43:40,920 --> 00:43:43,880
I love it. Such harmony. Mashallah.

547
00:43:46,680 --> 00:43:49,880
You were at each other’s throats just a minute ago. What happened?

548
00:43:51,200 --> 00:43:54,720
That’s normal between siblings, mom.

549
00:43:58,080 --> 00:44:03,000
You need to rest. You can’t work like this.

550
00:44:03,000 --> 00:44:07,600
Your health comes first. No working.

551
00:44:11,200 --> 00:44:13,760
Fine. I guess I’ll rest.

552
00:44:14,960 --> 00:44:16,200
Orders from above.

553
00:44:23,000 --> 00:44:24,160
Can I drink my soup now?

554
00:44:25,040 --> 00:44:25,600
Ask Çiçek.

555
00:44:28,120 --> 00:44:31,680
Enjoy it, mom. Don’t let it cool.

556
00:44:56,560 --> 00:44:57,800
Can we talk?

557
00:45:01,800 --> 00:45:03,240
I asked you something. Will you answer?

558
00:45:06,480 --> 00:45:07,840
Mercan, can’t you hear me?

559
00:45:08,480 --> 00:45:09,400
Why are you shouting?

560
00:45:09,520 --> 00:45:10,240
I’m not.

561
00:45:10,640 --> 00:45:11,800
You are. Get a grip.

562
00:45:13,840 --> 00:45:15,360
Look at me when I’m talking.

563
00:45:22,000 --> 00:45:22,400
I’m not looking.

564
00:45:23,760 --> 00:45:24,240
Should I force you?

565
00:45:25,160 --> 00:45:27,320
If needed. Don’t drive me crazy.

566
00:45:29,840 --> 00:45:32,800
It’s my job. It’s in my job description.

567
00:45:33,040 --> 00:45:35,240
Then revise that description.

568
00:45:36,800 --> 00:45:41,160
No. I’m fine as I am.

569
00:45:43,720 --> 00:45:45,000
Drop the stubbornness and look at me.

570
00:45:46,880 --> 00:45:47,560
I said look at me.

571
00:45:49,360 --> 00:45:52,120
I am. Speak.

572
00:45:53,440 --> 00:45:54,360
Why are you like this?

573
00:45:55,800 --> 00:45:56,240
Like what?

574
00:45:56,960 --> 00:45:59,800
What’s wrong with you? You were strange at dinner.

575
00:46:00,480 --> 00:46:02,000
You have no patience for me.

576
00:46:03,040 --> 00:46:03,920
That’s not true.

577
00:46:04,840 --> 00:46:05,720
Where did you get that?

578
00:46:06,200 --> 00:46:06,920
From your attitude.

579
00:46:07,920 --> 00:46:10,040
You avoid me, snap at me.

580
00:46:10,480 --> 00:46:12,080
You leave without saying anything.

581
00:46:12,360 --> 00:46:14,320
You don’t even want to eat at the same table.

582
00:46:18,600 --> 00:46:19,320
Don’t…

583
00:46:19,520 --> 00:46:22,600
Don’t tell me I misunderstood. I know what I lived.

584
00:46:28,560 --> 00:46:29,560
You understood perfectly.

585
00:46:34,640 --> 00:46:36,040
I can’t stand you anymore.

586
00:46:41,720 --> 00:46:46,400
Seeing you, being near you, bothers me.

587
00:46:46,680 --> 00:46:47,280
Too much.

588
00:46:50,240 --> 00:46:52,360
I can’t stand you anymore.

589
00:47:02,200 --> 00:47:02,840
Okay.

590
00:47:07,120 --> 00:47:09,160
If my presence bothers you so much.

591
00:47:11,640 --> 00:47:13,080
I’ll leave you alone.

592
00:47:28,840 --> 00:47:29,880
What did I just say?

593
00:47:31,240 --> 00:47:33,800
Why did I speak like that?

594
00:47:48,320 --> 00:47:49,840
What would I even say if I left?

595
00:48:06,920 --> 00:48:08,680
I can’t stand you anymore.

596
00:48:09,960 --> 00:48:13,720
Seeing you, being near you, bothers me.

597
00:48:14,240 --> 00:48:15,360
Too much.

598
00:48:23,120 --> 00:48:30,160
Değmen benim gamlı yaslı gönlüme.

599
00:48:31,920 --> 00:48:38,640
Değmen benim gamlı yaslı gönlüme.

600
00:48:39,680 --> 00:48:46,160
Ben bir selvi boylu yardan ayrıldım.

601
00:48:46,160 --> 00:48:51,480
Ayrıldım, ayrıldım, ayrıldım.

602
00:48:51,800 --> 00:48:54,480
You are close enough to touch.

603
00:48:55,720 --> 00:48:55,920
Ben bir selvi boylu yardan ayrıldım.

604
00:48:55,920 --> 00:48:59,200
Yet too far to reunite.

605
00:48:59,200 --> 00:49:02,040
Ben bir selvi boylu yardan ayrıldım.

606
00:49:02,040 --> 00:49:03,880
To long for someone while side by side is harder than separation.

607
00:49:03,880 --> 00:49:05,240
Ayrıldım, ayrıldım, ayrıldım. To long for someone while side by side is harder than separation. To long for someone while side by side is harder than separation.

608
00:49:08,120 --> 00:49:10,360
My God, help me.

609
00:49:12,040 --> 00:49:18,240
Evvel baban idim dostun bağında.

610
00:49:19,800 --> 00:49:21,200
What will I do now?

611
00:49:25,160 --> 00:49:27,800
Mom, why did you get up?

612
00:49:30,280 --> 00:49:31,800
I’m fine now, my daughter.

613
00:49:32,640 --> 00:49:34,200
Shall I make you something to drink?

614
00:49:34,840 --> 00:49:36,440
No, thank you.

615
00:49:37,320 --> 00:49:39,640
Why are you walking around?

616
00:49:40,360 --> 00:49:42,760
I couldn’t sleep.

617
00:49:43,280 --> 00:49:46,840
I thought I’d get some air.

618
00:49:46,960 --> 00:49:48,680
It’s cold outside.

619
00:49:51,520 --> 00:49:52,680
Was it Malik singing?

620
00:49:55,400 --> 00:49:56,240
I don’t know.

621
00:50:00,240 --> 00:50:01,880
I’ll go to bed then.

622
00:50:02,520 --> 00:50:03,320
Good night.

623
00:50:03,680 --> 00:50:04,800
Good night, my daughter.

624
00:50:05,080 --> 00:50:06,160
You should sleep too.

625
00:50:07,200 --> 00:50:07,840
Okay.

626
00:50:13,200 --> 00:50:17,440
My Lord, show me and my children the right path.

627
00:50:22,760 --> 00:50:24,160
Protect my children.

628
00:50:40,480 --> 00:50:42,600
Maybe I’ll sleep if I drink some milk.

629
00:50:44,240 --> 00:50:45,440
She didn’t come to the room at night.

630
00:50:46,200 --> 00:50:47,160
Who knows where she is.

631
00:50:56,120 --> 00:50:56,920
She’s here.

632
00:51:10,480 --> 00:51:11,560
What should I do now?

633
00:51:11,560 --> 00:51:17,400
It’s fine. Take your milk and leave, act normal.

634
00:51:17,880 --> 00:51:19,000
Coffee’s ready.

635
00:51:50,040 --> 00:51:51,080
Just how you like it.

636
00:51:55,840 --> 00:51:56,360
Thank you.

637
00:52:04,200 --> 00:52:06,600
So the gentleman is having coffee with Monika.

638
00:52:08,520 --> 00:52:09,400
Couldn’t sleep?

639
00:52:10,480 --> 00:52:11,440
No.

640
00:52:13,360 --> 00:52:13,920
Me neither.

641
00:52:23,200 --> 00:52:23,840
What are you doing?

642
00:52:24,600 --> 00:52:26,120
Hey.

643
00:52:28,960 --> 00:52:30,600
There was dust, I wiped it.

644
00:52:34,280 --> 00:52:36,320
Well, good night.

645
00:52:37,440 --> 00:52:38,440
Good night.

646
00:52:42,680 --> 00:52:44,640
We were having coffee too, Ateş and I.

647
00:52:46,520 --> 00:52:47,360
Enjoy.

648
00:52:48,400 --> 00:52:49,040
Thanks.

649
00:53:03,680 --> 00:53:04,640
Couldn’t sleep?

650
00:53:06,480 --> 00:53:06,840
No.

651
00:53:08,560 --> 00:53:09,520
I was sleeping actually.

652
00:53:10,720 --> 00:53:13,320
But there was noise.

653
00:53:13,640 --> 00:53:17,280
I came down to check who was making noise.

654
00:53:18,360 --> 00:53:19,080
It was you.

655
00:53:22,120 --> 00:53:23,520
You’re hearing a lot of things lately.

656
00:53:27,400 --> 00:53:29,320
Sorry if we woke you.

657
00:53:31,240 --> 00:53:32,520
No problem.

658
00:53:34,000 --> 00:53:35,160
I sleep lightly.

659
00:53:37,040 --> 00:53:39,440
I woke up, but I’ll go back to sleep.

660
00:53:39,600 --> 00:53:40,560
Like a baby.

661
00:53:40,960 --> 00:53:41,640
No problem at all.

662
00:53:45,960 --> 00:53:49,040
By the way, am I bothering you?

663
00:53:49,320 --> 00:53:50,920
I’ll leave as soon as the milk heats up.

664
00:53:51,120 --> 00:53:52,320
Right away.

665
00:53:53,440 --> 00:53:55,480
No, you’re not bothering us.

666
00:53:58,920 --> 00:54:00,040
Maybe I am.

667
00:54:04,560 --> 00:54:06,520
No, you’re not.

668
00:54:06,840 --> 00:54:09,800
But if you want, go to bed. I’ll bring the milk.

669
00:54:15,320 --> 00:54:17,320
Thanks, no need. How thoughtful.

670
00:54:20,480 --> 00:54:22,480
Of course not. You’re a guest.

671
00:54:24,160 --> 00:54:25,560
So, when are you leaving?

672
00:54:27,040 --> 00:54:27,640
I don’t know.

673
00:54:28,440 --> 00:54:30,480
Ateş will show me around Istanbul.

674
00:54:30,520 --> 00:54:31,960
I’ll break his hand.

675
00:54:32,840 --> 00:54:33,800
I missed it so much.

676
00:54:35,800 --> 00:54:36,200
Of course.

677
00:54:37,160 --> 00:54:38,320
Who doesn’t miss Istanbul?

678
00:54:38,960 --> 00:54:39,840
Go ahead, tour it.

679
00:54:40,120 --> 00:54:41,080
That’d be nice.

680
00:54:41,080 --> 00:54:45,320
But Istanbul isn’t what it used to be.

681
00:54:46,920 --> 00:54:48,400
It’s too crowded now.

682
00:54:52,480 --> 00:54:53,880
Best not add to it.

683
00:55:00,880 --> 00:55:02,480
The milk is hot.

684
00:55:02,680 --> 00:55:04,240
Very hot.

685
00:55:19,560 --> 00:55:21,400
Want a refill?

686
00:55:25,920 --> 00:55:26,440
No need.

687
00:55:29,200 --> 00:55:30,120
Clingy thing.

688
00:55:38,880 --> 00:55:39,600
Mercan.

689
00:55:40,560 --> 00:55:41,080
Yes?

690
00:55:48,600 --> 00:55:49,400
You forgot the milk.

691
00:56:07,680 --> 00:56:09,640
Oh, sorry.

692
00:56:24,440 --> 00:56:25,360
God forgive me.

693
00:56:33,000 --> 00:56:34,000
Come, Cemal.

694
00:56:34,200 --> 00:56:35,000
Where were you?

695
00:56:36,200 --> 00:56:38,560
Sorry, work ran late.

696
00:56:38,880 --> 00:56:41,480
I kept her company while you were gone.

697
00:56:42,640 --> 00:56:44,720
That’s how it went. You should sleep now.

698
00:56:45,120 --> 00:56:47,320
It’s late. Cemal and I will work a bit.

699
00:56:48,720 --> 00:56:50,480
All right. I’ll sleep.

700
00:56:51,000 --> 00:56:52,920
Okay. Good night.

701
00:56:53,520 --> 00:56:54,320
Good night.

702
00:57:03,160 --> 00:57:04,400
She wore you down, didn’t she?

703
00:57:05,240 --> 00:57:06,200
Don’t ask.

704
00:57:07,400 --> 00:57:11,160
Thank God Mercan came, my time improved.

705
00:57:12,800 --> 00:57:14,040
My time improved.

706
00:57:14,040 --> 00:57:17,600
My God, learning new phrases at this age.

707
00:57:19,000 --> 00:57:20,120
Come on.

708
00:57:20,400 --> 00:57:22,160
Let’s get to work. To the study.

709
00:57:56,960 --> 00:57:58,080
She didn’t come all night.

710
00:57:59,440 --> 00:58:00,800
Look at the time.

711
00:58:01,880 --> 00:58:02,680
Still not back.

712
00:58:06,560 --> 00:58:09,320
Where did the gentleman put out his light last night?

713
00:58:20,200 --> 00:58:22,520
You’ve invaded my heart.

714
00:58:22,520 --> 00:58:24,520
I love you, I love you.

715
00:58:27,120 --> 00:58:28,160
Try to understand.

716
00:58:31,040 --> 00:58:32,360
You say all this…

717
00:58:33,480 --> 00:58:35,840
Then give up at the first crisis.

718
00:58:37,200 --> 00:58:38,800
That’s how much your love is worth.

719
00:58:41,960 --> 00:58:43,680
If you trust Ateş, you’re wasting it.

720
00:58:44,000 --> 00:58:46,840
One day he loves, the next he turns his back.

721
00:58:47,640 --> 00:58:48,600
He erases you.

722
00:58:57,560 --> 00:58:59,920
At least he told the truth.

723
00:59:08,520 --> 00:59:09,880
Pull yourself together, Mercan.

724
00:59:11,200 --> 00:59:15,120
It’s not worth sorrow or regret over a fickle man.

725
00:59:16,760 --> 00:59:18,040
Why did you believe him anyway?

726
00:59:32,440 --> 00:59:32,880
Good morning.

727
00:59:33,480 --> 00:59:34,720
Morning.

728
00:59:39,080 --> 00:59:41,200
You didn’t come to the room last night.

729
00:59:41,960 --> 00:59:42,480
Yes.

730
00:59:43,280 --> 00:59:43,800
Where were you?

731
00:59:44,880 --> 00:59:46,120
In the kitchen. You saw.

732
00:59:47,640 --> 00:59:49,240
We continued working there.

733
00:59:51,400 --> 00:59:52,120
You worked.

734
00:59:53,080 --> 00:59:53,880
We worked.

735
00:59:54,520 --> 00:59:55,960
You could’ve stayed too.

736
00:59:56,960 --> 00:59:57,320
No.

737
00:59:58,320 --> 01:00:00,120
I don’t want to be a bother.

738
01:00:01,840 --> 01:00:02,840
Why would you be?

739
01:00:02,880 --> 01:00:03,760
Are we strangers?

740
01:00:04,920 --> 01:00:05,840
You’re right.

741
01:00:05,840 --> 01:00:08,000
You were never strangers.

742
01:00:08,080 --> 01:00:09,680
You were quite close.

743
01:00:11,720 --> 01:00:13,160
We’ve known each other for years.

744
01:00:13,200 --> 01:00:14,360
Of course we’re close.

745
01:00:15,320 --> 01:00:16,360
Why are you surprised?

746
01:00:17,720 --> 01:00:18,760
You have no issue with it.

747
01:00:18,880 --> 01:00:20,960
I get that, just don’t say it to me.

748
01:00:21,560 --> 01:00:22,560
Why? What is it?

749
01:00:23,520 --> 01:00:24,080
True.
True.

750
01:00:24,840 --> 01:00:26,200
You’re right. Who am I anyway?

751
01:00:26,280 --> 01:00:26,960
I’m nothing.

752
01:00:27,760 --> 01:00:28,200
True.

753
01:00:29,000 --> 01:00:30,840
You didn’t understand why I reacted like that?

754
01:00:31,080 --> 01:00:32,520
Do we have secrets?

755
01:00:33,520 --> 01:00:37,880
If you don’t get even this, there’s nothing I can do.

756
01:00:39,400 --> 01:00:41,160
Since you didn’t come to the room all night.

757
01:00:42,200 --> 01:00:43,360
I guess you didn’t sleep.

758
01:00:43,800 --> 01:00:44,320
Yes.

759
01:00:45,480 --> 01:00:45,920
Wow.

760
01:00:46,560 --> 01:00:47,280
Wow indeed.

761
01:00:48,920 --> 01:00:49,920
What did you do then?

762
01:00:52,480 --> 01:00:56,520
You must’ve done more than talk all night.

763
01:00:57,200 --> 01:00:58,080
I don’t know.

764
01:00:59,240 --> 01:01:00,880
I said we worked.

765
01:01:00,880 --> 01:01:03,440
Then we had coffee and talked.

766
01:01:04,560 --> 01:01:05,840
We fell asleep on the couch.

767
01:01:07,720 --> 01:01:08,160
On the couch?

768
01:01:09,360 --> 01:01:10,880
You slept together?

769
01:01:12,840 --> 01:01:14,240
Side by side?

770
01:01:15,960 --> 01:01:18,280
What are you implying?

771
01:01:18,920 --> 01:01:20,840
Speak plainly. Where are you going with this?

772
01:01:21,520 --> 01:01:22,160
Nowhere.

773
01:01:23,600 --> 01:01:25,720
Neither of us will get anywhere like this.

774
01:01:30,240 --> 01:01:32,960
I wish you lifelong happiness with your friend.

775
01:01:40,800 --> 01:01:42,240
With Cemal?

776
01:01:43,640 --> 01:01:44,280
What does that have to do with anything?

777
01:02:26,320 --> 01:02:28,400
Aunt Nermin.

778
01:02:30,160 --> 01:02:31,400
Hello Demet, how are you?

779
01:02:34,760 --> 01:02:36,880
Welcome, what a nice surprise.

780
01:02:39,960 --> 01:02:42,040
Come, let’s sit.

781
01:02:56,920 --> 01:02:58,560
How’s work?

782
01:02:59,080 --> 01:03:00,800
We’re good, very busy.

783
01:03:02,920 --> 01:03:05,240
New employees started, I guess.

784
01:03:12,040 --> 01:03:15,320
I saw a young man your age at the mansion.

785
01:03:16,000 --> 01:03:16,680
Who was he?

786
01:03:17,720 --> 01:03:18,400
Burak?

787
01:03:19,400 --> 01:03:20,880
Yes, Burak.

788
01:03:22,360 --> 01:03:24,360
He looked familiar.

789
01:03:25,240 --> 01:03:29,440
I couldn’t place him then, but later he reminded me of someone.

790
01:03:30,080 --> 01:03:31,200
Who was he connected to?

791
01:03:32,200 --> 01:03:35,240
I’m not sure, but I can call HR.

792
01:03:36,200 --> 01:03:38,560
I’d appreciate it.

793
01:03:38,920 --> 01:03:41,440
It’s been on my mind.

794
01:03:51,160 --> 01:03:55,240
Hello, could you send Burak Yücel’s CV?

795
01:03:56,760 --> 01:03:57,560
Thank you.

796
01:03:58,080 --> 01:03:58,480
It’s coming.

797
01:04:14,120 --> 01:04:15,040
Come here.

798
01:04:15,160 --> 01:04:17,920
What are you doing? What are you doing?

799
01:04:18,840 --> 01:04:19,720
What did I do?

800
01:04:20,400 --> 01:04:22,000
What do you want from my brother?

801
01:04:23,760 --> 01:04:24,440
What would I want?

802
01:04:24,680 --> 01:04:25,520
His heart.

803
01:04:26,280 --> 01:04:27,480
His heart?

804
01:04:28,440 --> 01:04:30,120
We love each other.

805
01:04:30,640 --> 01:04:32,280
Are you mocking me?

806
01:04:32,520 --> 01:04:33,160
No.

807
01:04:33,680 --> 01:04:35,640
You loved Malik until yesterday.

808
01:04:36,320 --> 01:04:38,000
Malik? Who’s that?

809
01:04:39,280 --> 01:04:43,480
What kind of person are you?

810
01:04:43,960 --> 01:04:46,040
You were plotting to break us up.

811
01:04:46,400 --> 01:04:48,360
What changed, suddenly you’re in love with my brother?

812
01:04:48,880 --> 01:04:52,600
Malik was a mistake. I wasn’t in love with him.

813
01:04:52,600 --> 01:04:53,960
Of course.

814
01:04:54,280 --> 01:04:56,360
That’s why you tried to split us?

815
01:04:57,800 --> 01:05:00,960
The past is past, sweetheart. We’re looking ahead.

816
01:05:02,040 --> 01:05:02,720
Listen, Zehra.

817
01:05:05,120 --> 01:05:07,600
Be a little understanding.

818
01:05:08,240 --> 01:05:09,920
You don’t play with people’s feelings.

819
01:05:10,400 --> 01:05:12,320
I’m not playing with anyone’s feelings.

820
01:05:12,920 --> 01:05:14,840
I fell for your brother. What should I do?

821
01:05:15,120 --> 01:05:16,080
Tell my heart to stop?

822
01:05:16,800 --> 01:05:19,840
Oh please. What love?

823
01:05:20,200 --> 01:05:21,840
I don’t have to convince you.

824
01:05:21,840 --> 01:05:23,120
You do.

825
01:05:24,640 --> 01:05:27,960
You’re right. Actually, you don’t.

826
01:05:29,200 --> 01:05:31,120
We’ll pretend none of this happened.

827
01:05:32,000 --> 01:05:33,960
You’ll leave my brother.

828
01:05:35,240 --> 01:05:36,360
Because you say so?

829
01:05:36,760 --> 01:05:38,120
Yes, because I want it.

830
01:05:38,760 --> 01:05:39,880
Give up this love.

831
01:05:40,280 --> 01:05:44,040
Or you’ll get hurt badly.

832
01:05:45,520 --> 01:05:47,160
Are you threatening me?

833
01:05:47,680 --> 01:05:49,920
Yes, I am.

834
01:05:49,920 --> 01:05:52,640
Just like you did before.

835
01:05:54,720 --> 01:05:55,880
What do you mean?

836
01:05:56,160 --> 01:05:57,720
Stay away from my brother.

837
01:05:59,640 --> 01:06:02,120
Or I’ll tell him about Malik…

838
01:06:02,480 --> 01:06:07,000
and all the plans you made to break us up.

839
01:06:20,720 --> 01:06:21,520
Here you go, Ms. Demet.

840
01:06:22,120 --> 01:06:24,440
I’ll look. Don’t let me keep you.

841
01:06:49,400 --> 01:06:51,960
I was right.

842
01:07:00,840 --> 01:07:01,800
What now?

843
01:07:02,280 --> 01:07:04,800
What will I do? What is this boy planning?

844
01:07:09,840 --> 01:07:12,080
I have to go, Demet.

845
01:07:12,480 --> 01:07:14,320
I’ll walk you out, aunt Nermin.

846
01:07:33,400 --> 01:07:36,480
Yaşar, aunt Nermin came to see Demet.

847
01:07:36,560 --> 01:07:37,600
Why? Do you know?

848
01:07:38,920 --> 01:07:39,600
I don’t.

849
01:07:41,480 --> 01:07:43,720
But she asked about you.

850
01:07:45,520 --> 01:07:46,160
Really?

851
01:08:03,240 --> 01:08:05,600
I don’t understand this girl.

852
01:08:06,520 --> 01:08:09,760
One moment careless, next questioning.

853
01:08:12,640 --> 01:08:14,000
What was that just now?

854
01:08:16,000 --> 01:08:17,400
She interrogated me.

855
01:08:18,760 --> 01:08:21,080
All but put me in the defendant’s chair.

856
01:08:23,600 --> 01:08:24,400
If you don’t love me…

857
01:08:25,440 --> 01:08:27,600
and say we’re impossible, why all these questions?

858
01:08:28,120 --> 01:08:31,600
If you do love me, why leave me and go alone?

859
01:08:35,080 --> 01:08:37,320
You need a manual to understand women.

860
01:08:38,240 --> 01:08:40,720
I wish someone wrote one.

861
01:08:59,240 --> 01:09:00,280
I mean…

862
01:09:02,240 --> 01:09:03,800
I ask, she doesn’t deny.

863
01:09:08,480 --> 01:09:10,960
Then she says they passed out on the couch.

864
01:09:15,360 --> 01:09:16,520
How not to go crazy?

865
01:09:16,520 --> 01:09:18,720
This is too much.

866
01:09:33,440 --> 01:09:36,240
Ateş protected you once or twice, gave you courage.

867
01:09:37,640 --> 01:09:38,640
But take it from me.

868
01:09:40,760 --> 01:09:41,680
Don’t trust him too much.

869
01:09:42,800 --> 01:09:45,240
For him, one goes, another comes.

870
01:09:53,480 --> 01:09:54,680
I trusted him.

871
01:09:56,600 --> 01:09:58,680
Turns out he’s not trustworthy.

872
01:10:03,840 --> 01:10:07,600
Then why am I this upset?

873
01:10:34,080 --> 01:10:35,320
Where is the charger?

874
01:11:53,040 --> 01:11:55,240
She framed our photo.

875
01:12:01,640 --> 01:12:03,720
So it matters to her.

876
01:13:12,520 --> 01:13:13,120
It’s beautiful.

877
01:13:16,280 --> 01:13:17,160
It really is.

878
01:13:21,880 --> 01:13:23,640
Who did she buy it for?

879
01:13:28,000 --> 01:13:28,960
Could it be for me?

880
01:13:30,480 --> 01:13:32,120
To replace my broken necklace?

881
01:13:52,360 --> 01:13:53,160
Or…
